name: Valencia en Detalle - set of seven postcards.
description:
Set of seven A6 postcards.

Valencia en Detalle. 
A collection of seven images from the streets of Valencia - Textures, tiles and typography. The detail and patina of the city captured when exploring its sunny streets - Finding beauty from the everyday and the traces people leave behind...
An alternative souvenir to the typical postcards.
Buy as a set, a memento of Valencia.

Una colección de siete imágenes de las calles de Valencia - Texturas, azulejos y tipografía. Capturan el detalle y pátina que adquiere la ciudad al recorrer sus calles soleadas. Descubriendo la belleza de lo cotidiano y la huella que la gente deja tras de sí... Un recuerdo y una alternativa a las típicas postales asociadas a la ciudad.
Se pueden comprar como colección, un souvenir de Valencia.

name: Sp*m Heads
description:
A6 concertina hand screen printed book.

Kavel Rafferty created SPAM HEAD; portraits based on the strange and sometimes wonderful names that arrive uninvited in her email inbox every day, trying to sell her designer replica watches, viagra and other such nonsense. She wanted to make portraits for these funny faceless folk and so started to hand draw in pen and then scan the reverse side of the paper with her faithful old scanner in order to get the desired fuzzy quality of line. The result is a delightful collection of 13 imaginary personalities contained in a concertina book hand screenprinted in an edition of just 100 copies. Each one is signed and numbered by Kavel.

name: Alphabet poster by Marcus Walters
description:
A beautiful full colour lithographic print of the alphabet created by Marcus Walters. Each letter features a different object or animal illustrated by Marcus's distinctive collage style, and reproduced in all its detail.

The poster is 70cm x 50cm (27.5" x 19.75") and fits most off the shelf frames (Ikea, Habitat etc). Printed on 250 gsm Cyclus Offset 100% recycled stock. Posted in super thick cardboard postal tube.

name: 123 poster by Marcus Walters
description:
A lovely lithographic print. Each number features a different animal or insect with a subtle counting aspect.

The poster is A3 size and fits in most off-the-shelf frames (Ikea, Habitat etc). Printed using Vegetable and Soy based inks on 250 gsm Cyclus Offset 100% recycled stock. Posted in super thick cardboard postal tube.

Marcus would be happy to write a child's name by request on the top left hand corner. Please specify when ordering.

Perfect alongside the Alphabet poster in any nursery or children's bedroom!

9.50 €

description:
'We are planning something else' specially designed for the Mama Cat Trust. 
http://www.mamacat.co.uk/
Limited edition of 100 high quality A3 digitally printed poster.

The Mama Cat Trust is based in the U.K. but carries out most of it's work with feral and street cats in the Cambrils area of Spain. 
The Mama cat trust promotes responsible and humane treatment of all animals and the implementation of neutering programmes focusing on feral and stray cats.

All profit goes to the mama cat trust.

name: por tables place mats
description:
Set of 6 'por tables' photographic place mats by Ella Doran and Kavel Rafferty.

Ella Doran and Kavel Rafferty have joined forces for a very special, vintage vinyl-inspired pop art project. Ella and Kavel have used portable record players from their own homes and from their music aficionado friends to create this irresistible tableware collection. Drawing influence from the textures, colours and simple style of these classic mid-20th century designs, Ella and Kavel fuse these classic forms with lost and found formica for a modern-retro feel to make anybody’s table – music fanatic or not – sing.

Size 24cm x 19cm
Teh mats are uniquely hand made in the UK.
Wipe down surface. Do not immerse in water.

name: 'JULY' Hello Kitten print
description:
'JULY' A3 fine art digital print, signed and numbered limited edition of 20. Printed with archival Inks on watercolour paper.

***Perfect for an April Birthday gift***

The 'Hello Kitten' project began when Kavel Rafferty found a bundle of late 50s Swedish erotic magazines at a local flea market. Kavel has combined inky drawings of her favorite women with the other calendar staple, kittens, (the kittens come from her vintage postcard collection) left over remnants of paint palettes and found imagery to make these slightly surreal and beautiful mix media collages. Kavel has played with scale and colour in these 'popporn' images creating one calendar girl for every month of the year.
